==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ophelic
<hw>O*phel"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a substance (called <xex>ophelic
acid</xex>) extracted from a plant (<gen>Ophelia</gen>) of the Gentian
family as a bitter yellowish sirup, used in India as a febrifuge and
tonic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ophicleide</ent>⟦br⟧
